def_cn: （产业、服务）私立的，私有的，私营的，民营的
def_en: Private industries and services are owned or controlled by an individual person or a commercial company, rather than by the state or an official organization.
Private individuals are acting only for themselves, and are not representing any group, company, or organization.

def_cn: （财物等）个人所有的，私有的，私人的
def_en: Your private things belong only to you, or may only be used by you.

def_cn: （地方、聚会等）非公开的，私人的
def_en: Private places or gatherings may be attended only by a particular group of people, rather than by the general public.

def_cn: （会议、讨论、活动等）秘密的，私下的
def_en: Private meetings, discussions, and other activities involve only a small number of people, and very little information about them is given to other people.

def_cn: （生活）私人的，个人的，与工作无关的
def_en: Your private life is that part of your life that is concerned with your personal relationships and activities, rather than with your work or business.

def_cn: （想法、感觉）私密的，隐私的，内心的
def_en: Your private thoughts or feelings are ones that you do not talk about to other people.
You can use private to describe situations or activities that are understood only by the people involved in them, and not by anyone else.

def_cn: （地方等）僻静的，幽静的，无人打扰的
def_en: If you describe a place as private, or as somewhere where you can be private, you mean that it is a quiet place and you can be alone there without being disturbed.

def_cn: （人）内敛的，文静内向的，孤僻的
def_en: If you describe someone as a private person, you mean that they are very quiet by nature and do not reveal their thoughts and feelings to other people.

def_cn: 私人教授的；私下辅导的
def_en: You can use private to describe lessons that are not part of ordinary school activity, and which are given by a teacher to an individual pupil or a small group, usually in return for payment.

def_cn: 列兵，二等兵（级别最低的士兵）
def_en: A private is a soldier of the lowest rank in an army or the marines.
If you do something in private, you do it without other people being present, often because it is something that you want to keep secret.
